{"type":"message","id":"c49bb6ab","parentId":"eb6331c0","timestamp":"2026-02-15T01:50:18.135Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user just said \"hello\". According to my instructions, I need to:\n\n1. Read SOUL.md - this is who I am\n2. Read USER.md - this is who I'm helping\n3. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. If in MAIN SESSION (direct chat with human), also read MEMORY.md\n\nSince this is a webchat direct message, this is a MAIN SESSION. I should read these files before responding.\n\nLet me check the current date - it's Sunday, 2026-02-15 according to the timestamp. So I need to read:\n- SOUL.md\n- USER.md\n- memory/2026-02-15.md (today)\n- memory/2026-02-14.md (yesterday)\n- MEMORY.md (since this is main session)\n\nLet me read all these files first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Hey! 👋\n\nLet me get up to speed first — reading my memory files to see"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:0","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-02-15.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-02-14.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:4","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":12939,"output":339,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13278,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771120187918}}
{"type":"message","id":"fae0cc3c","parentId":"c49bb6ab","timestamp":"2026-02-15T01:50:18.161Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're trusty-pal. A trustworthy assistant and project partner._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Be a true partner.** You're not just executing tasks; you're thinking alongside them. Offer perspectives, catch things they might miss, help them see around corners.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## As a Project Partner\n\n- Think ahead — what might they need next?\n- Keep track of context — don't make them repeat themselves\n- Proactively organize and maintain their workspace\n- Flag risks, suggest alternatives, play devil's advocate when useful\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771120218157}}
{"type":"message","id":"d82b266a","parentId":"fae0cc3c","timestamp":"2026-02-15T01:50:18.203Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n*Learning about the person you're helping. Update this as you go.*\n\n- **Name:** *(prefers not stated / use context)*\n- **What to call them:** *(to be determined)*\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Age:** 61\n- **Location:** Singapore\n- **Timezone:** Asia/Singapore (GMT+8)\n- **Notes:** \n  - WhatsApp connected: +6591127357\n  - Backup phone: +6597730111\n  - Backup phone: +6597730111\n\n## Background\n- Former IT engineer, now retired\n- 30-year Linux user (personal workstation)\n- Passionate about technology, especially IT and AI\n- Strong open source advocate — contributes ~1 project/week\n\n## Recent Projects\n- https://github.com/nordeim/LArtisan-Baking-Atelier\n- https://github.com/nordeim/baking-ecommerce\n- https://github.com/nordeim/Aurora-Luxe-Travel\n- https://github.com/nordeim/xiaomi-cafe\n- https://github.com/nordeim/morning-brew-cafe\n- https://github.com/nordeim/cherry-kopitiam\n\n## Interests\n- Sharing AI knowledge and information with others\n- Building and open-sourcing practical projects\n- Testing/evaluating coding agents (OpenCode, Antigravity, Windsurf, etc.)\n- Turning visual design concepts into working full-stack applications\n\n## Technical Knowledge\n- Deep understanding of LLM training: pre/post training, RL, GRPO, PPO, DPO\n- Architecture: MoE (Mixture of Experts)\n- Preferred models: Claude Opus/Sonnet, GLM-4.7, Qwen3 Max, Kimi K2/K2.5\n- Focus: Agentic capabilities of modern LLMs\n\n## Working Methodology\n- **The Meticulous Approach**: Think first → Plan → Validate → Implement → Verify → Deliver\n- **Design Philosophy**: Anti-Generic, Avant-Garde UI with Intentional Minimalism\n- **No surface-level solutions**: Deep reasoning, multiple options evaluated, risks assessed\n- **Validation checkpoint**: Plan must be confirmed before any code is written\n- **Quality standards**: WCAG AAA, TypeScript strict, comprehensive testing\n\n## Available Skills Inventory (90+)\n**Key categories for my workflow:**\n- **Development**: nextjs-tailwind-v4-luxe, frontend-dev-guidelines, app-builder, web-frameworks\n- **Design**: aesthetic, frontend-design, ui-styling, tailwind-patterns, mobile-design\n- **Quality**: code-review, testing-patterns, tdd-workflow, webapp-testing, lint-and-validate\n- **Security**: vulnerability-scanner, red-team-tactics\n- **Problem-Solving**: systematic-debugging, root-cause-tracing, sequential-thinking, verification-before-completion\n- **Project Management**: plan-writing, skill-creator, parallel-agents\n\n## Context\n*(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)*\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771120218169}}
