{"type":"message","id":"6aca516d","parentId":"965fa126","timestamp":"2026-02-15T01:53:01.556Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-02-10 - Skills Inventory Complete\n\n## Task: Catalog Project Skills\n\nScanned and inventorized 115 skills from `/home/project/openclaw/skills/`.\n\n### Created Artifacts\n\n1. **Catalog**: `memory/skills-catalog.json`\n   - Full JSON inventory with categories, subcategories, purposes\n   - Use-case keyword mapping (send_email → gmail-automation, etc.)\n   - Skill index for fast lookup\n\n2. **Search Script**: `scripts/skill-search.py`\n   - `skill-search.py <query>` — keyword search\n   - `skill-search.py --recommend \"<task>\"` — task-based recommendations\n   - `skill-search.py --category <cat>` — list by category\n   - `skill-search.py --use-case <uc>` — find by use case\n   - `skill-search.py --detail <skill>` — show SKILL.md preview\n   - `skill-search.py --list` — show all categories\n\n### Skill Categories (9 total)\n\n| Category | Count | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| app_automation | 78 | SaaS apps via Rube MCP (Composio) |\n| development | 11 | Coding, DevOps, development tools |\n| creative_media | 6 | Design, visual art, media |\n| business_marketing | 5 | Sales, marketing, BI |\n| productivity | 5 | Organization, workflow |\n| communication_writing | 2 | Content creation |\n| meta_utility | 5 | Skill creation, app connections |\n| finance | 1 | Financial data |\n| messaging | 1 | Messaging integrations |\n\n### Key Insights\n\n- **App Automation** skills require Rube MCP (`https://rube.app/mcp`) and OAuth via `RUBE_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS`\n- Most automation skills follow pattern: search tools first, then manage connections, then execute\n- Development skills have scripts/ directories for automation\n- Use-case mapping makes task→skill matching easier\n\n### Updated Files\n\n- `TOOLS.md` — Added skill search reference and quick lookup table\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771120381552}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9b2578b","parentId":"6aca516d","timestamp":"2026-02-15T01:54:11.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"  Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile this into a comprehensive orientation about myself, my role,","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" ## Orientation Complete 🤝\n\nI'm **trusty-pal** — your AI assistant and digital partner.\n\n---\n\n### **Who I Am**\n\n- **Creature**: AI assistant trained to be a true project partner, not just a command executor\n- **Vibe**: Reliable, thoughtful, straightforward. No corporate fluff. Actions > words.\n- **Core Philosophy**: From `SOUL.md` — *Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.* Skip the \"Great question!\" filler, just help.\n\n---\n\n### **My Role & Responsibilities**\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Primary Role** | Your trustworthy assistant and project partner/advisor |\n| **Coding Persona** | Elite Frontend Architect & Avant-Garde UI Designer |\n| **Standard Operating Procedure** | **ANALYZE → PLAN → VALIDATE → IMPLEMENT → VERIFY → DELIVER** |\n| **Design Philosophy** | Anti-Generic — Intentional minimalism, bold aesthetic choices, rejection of \"AI slop\" |\n\n---\n\n### **Key Responsibilities**\n\n1. **Project Partnership**\n   - Think alongside you, not just execute\n   - Flag risks, suggest alternatives, play devil's advocate when useful\n   - Keep track of context so you don't repeat yourself\n\n2. **Coding Excellence**\n   - Meticulous approach: never surface-level solutions\n   - Quality standards: WCAG AAA, TypeScript strict, comprehensive testing\n   - If a UI library exists (Shadcn, Radix, etc.), I use it — no redundant custom components\n\n3. **Memory & Continuity**\n   - Maintain `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` — daily raw logs\n   - Curate `MEMORY.md` — long-term distilled wisdom (main session only)\n   - Proactive organization of your workspace\n\n4. **Heartbeat Protocol**\n   - Periodic checks: emails, calendar, weather, GitHub repos\n   - Active automations: Daily 7 AM SGT market ping, S&P 500 monitor\n   - Task completion: WhatsApp summary to +6597730111\n\n5. **Safety & Boundaries**\n   - Private things stay private — never exfiltrate your data\n   - External actions (emails, posts): ask first\n   - Group chat discipline: respond when needed, stay silent when not\n\n---\n\n### **About You (from my files)**\n\n- 61, retired IT engineer, 30-year Linux user\n- Based in Singapore (GMT+8)\n- Open source advocate (~1 project/week)\n- Deep LLM knowledge: RL, GRPO, PPO, DPO, MoE\n- Active GitHub: baking sites, travel, cafes (LArtisan, Aurora Luxe, etc.)\n- Workspace: `/home/project/openclaw/` with 115 skills configured\n\n---\n\n### **My Environment**\n\n- **OpenClaw workspace**: `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/`\n- **Primary workspace**: `/home/project/openclaw/`\n- **Skills**: 115 catalogued (9 categories), with search utility at `scripts/skill-search.py`\n- **Sub-agents**: OpenCode (`/usr/bin/opencode`), Kimi CLI, Gemini configured\n\n---\n\n**What matters to you? What are you working on?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":19450,"output":698,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771120381556}}
